fr.zelus.jarvis.core.session

Class JarvisContext

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.zelus.jarvis.core.session.JarvisContext

  • public class JarvisContext
extends Object
    A variable container bound to a JarvisSession.

    This class stores the different variables that can be set during user input processing and accessed by executed JarvisAction. JarvisContext is used to store:

    • InputProvider values such as the user name, the channel where the message was received, etc
    • Intent recognition values, that are computed by the Intent recognition engine and used to pass information between messages
    • Action values, that are returned by JarvisActions

    This class is heavily used by jarvis core component to pass JarvisAction parameters, and replace output message variables by their concrete values.

    • Method Detail

      • setContextValue

        public void setContextValue(String context,
                            String key,
                            Object value)
        Stores the provided value in the given context with the provided key.

        As an example, calling setContextValue("slack", "username", "myUsername") sets the variable username with the value myUsername in the slack context.

        To retrieve all the variables of a given sub-context see getContextVariables(String).

        Parameters:
        context - the sub-context to store the value in
        key - the sub-context key associated to the value
        value - the value to store
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the provided context or key is null
        See Also:
        getContextVariables(String), getContextValue(String, String)

      • getContextVariables

        public Map<String,Object> getContextVariables(String context)
        Returns all the variables stored in the given context.

        This method returns an unmodifiable Map holding the sub-context variables. To retrieve a specific variable from JarvisContext see getContextValue(String, String).

        Parameters:
        context - the sub-context to retrieve the variables from
        Returns:
        an unmodifiable Map holding the sub-context variables
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the provided context is null
        See Also:
        getContextValue(String, String)

      • getContextValue

        public Object getContextValue(String context,
                              String key)
        Returns the context value associated to the provided key.

        As an example, calling getContextValue("slack", "username") returns the value of the username variable stored in the slack sub-context.

        To retrieve all the variables of a given sub-context see getContextVariables(String).

        Parameters:
        context - the sub-context to retrieve the variable from
        key - the sub-context key associated to the value
        Returns:
        the context value associated to the provided key, or null if the key does not exist
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the provided context or key is null
        See Also:
        getContextVariables(String)

      • getContextMap

        protected Map<String,Map<String,Object>> getContextMap()
        Returns an unmodifiable Map representing the stored context values.

        Note: this method is protected for testing purposes, and should not be called by client code.

        Returns:
        an unmodifiable Map representing the stored context values
